the vacation doesn't go quite

00:24:28.520 --> 00:24:29.820
as planned.

00:24:29.820 --> 00:24:31.120
Yes?

00:24:31.120 --> 00:24:35.770
&gt;&gt; How did you think of the
characters in your books?

00:24:35.770 --> 00:24:38.490
&gt;&gt; Just in all of them or do
you have a specific book you're

00:24:38.490 --> 00:24:41.110
thinking about?

00:24:41.110 --> 00:24:42.410
&gt;&gt; More like Ever After High.

00:24:42.410 --> 00:24:45.680
&gt;&gt; Okay. So Ever After
High, actually was unusual

00:24:45.680 --> 00:24:49.460
because Mattel had
created this line of toys.

00:24:49.460 --> 00:24:51.590
And they were going to
make shows and they came

00:24:51.590 --> 00:24:54.570
to me before it was released,
it was so secret I had to sign

00:24:54.570 --> 00:24:55.870
on disclosure agreements.

00:24:55.870 --> 00:24:58.600
We had to use code
names, it was crazy,

00:24:58.600 --> 00:25:00.870
they flew me out to Mattel
headquarters in California,

00:25:00.870 --> 00:25:02.820
it was this big building
with no windows.

00:25:02.820 --> 00:25:05.890 position:56%
We went down like secret passageways
that had all of these like,

00:25:05.890 --> 00:25:07.190
codes to get in [inaudible].

00:25:07.190 --> 00:25:10.140
And when I saw the dolls
they were underneath a shroud

00:25:10.140 --> 00:25:11.890
and I could only like
peek under them.

00:25:11.890 --> 00:25:14.120
It was like, I felt like a spy.

00:25:14.120 --> 00:25:17.950 position:56%
Anyway, so they actually created
those characters and then, I came in

00:25:17.950 --> 00:25:20.630
and wrote the first book,
and we had such a great time.

00:25:20.630 --> 00:25:24.910 position:56%
I ended up writing 4 books for that,
but, in that case I didn't actually,

00:25:24.910 --> 00:25:28.270
I helped, I helped flush out
the characters, probably,

00:25:28.270 --> 00:25:30.850
but they had the initial
names and ideas.

00:25:30.850 --> 00:25:32.150
Right over here.

00:25:32.150 --> 00:25:34.690
&gt;&gt; How many super heroes
have you made?

00:25:34.690 --> 00:25:36.450
&gt;&gt; How many super heroes
have I made?

00:25:36.450 --> 00:25:39.200
I personally consider
every book I've written

00:25:39.200 --> 00:25:41.220
as being a super hero story.

00:25:41.220 --> 00:25:42.520
That's kind of my secret.

00:25:42.520 --> 00:25:44.670
They all feel like
super heroes to me.

00:25:44.670 --> 00:25:48.030
But I would, I guess, the Princess
in Black, the Squirrel Girl,

00:25:48.030 --> 00:25:50.330
I'm going to write a
Captain Marvel novel,

00:25:50.330 --> 00:25:52.090 position:56%
those would be my true super heroes.

00:25:52.090 --> 00:25:53.880
I wrote a young and old
book called Dangerous

00:25:53.880 --> 00:25:55.980
which was my super hero
science fiction novel.

00:25:55.980 --> 00:25:59.280
So, I don't know, a few dozen.

00:25:59.280 --> 00:26:00.580
I'm really good at math.

00:26:00.580 --> 00:26:01.880
Yes, right here.

00:26:01.880 --> 00:26:04.980
&gt;&gt; Why'd you name all of the
princesses after flowers?

00:26:04.980 --> 00:26:09.410
&gt;&gt; Oh, so Princess Magnolia,
is named after a flower

00:26:09.410 --> 00:26:12.960
because she's named after my
daughter whose name is Magnolia.

00:26:12.960 --> 00:26:15.590
And then when we had 12 more
princesses we thought it would be

00:26:15.590 --> 00:26:17.580
fun to continue that theme.

00:26:17.580 --> 00:26:19.270
And I just love flower names.

00:26:19.270 --> 00:26:20.570
Yes?

00:26:20.570 --> 00:26:22.820
&gt;&gt; What is Princess Academy about?

00:26:22.820 --> 00:26:26.870
&gt;&gt; Princess Academy is about a
village, at the top of a mountain,

00:26:26.870 --> 00:26:30.150
and the way they make a living is
they query stone, they cut blocks

00:26:30.150 --> 00:26:31.500
of stone out of the mountain.

00:26:31.500 --> 00:26:32.830
They're very poor.

00:26:32.830 --> 00:26:34.850
And one day a messenger
from the king comes up

00:26:34.850 --> 00:26:37.770
and says their village has
been chosen as the place

00:26:37.770 --> 00:26:39.970
where the next princess
will come from.

00:26:39.970 --> 00:26:42.710
And all of the girls, had
never been to school before,

00:26:42.710 --> 00:26:45.440
and they're all sent to a school,
called the Princess Academy

00:26:45.440 --> 00:26:47.930
to learn what they need to
know in case they are chosen.

00:26:47.930 --> 00:26:51.590
And they are reluctant about this,
they don't trust the low-landers,

00:26:51.590 --> 00:26:54.320
they don't really believe one of
them has to become a princess.

00:26:54.320 --> 00:26:55.760 position:56%
But in the process of learning stuff

00:26:55.760 --> 00:26:58.210
at the school, it changes
their life.

00:26:58.210 --> 00:26:59.510
Yes, right here.

00:26:59.510 --> 00:27:02.300
&gt;&gt; How did it make you feel
when you wrote the book?

00:27:02.300 --> 00:27:03.600
&gt;&gt; When I wrote a book?

00:27:03.600 --> 00:27:06.050
&gt;&gt; Yeah, when you wrote
Princess in Black.

00:27:06.050 --> 00:27:07.350
&gt;&gt; When I wrote Princess in Black.

00:27:07.350 --> 00:27:08.650
It made me feel like this.

00:27:08.650 --> 00:27:11.240
Yes, I love it.

00:27:11.240 --> 00:27:14.220
The one reason why I keep writing,
even though it's really hard,

00:27:14.220 --> 00:27:18.970 position:56%
for me and I make a lot of mistakes,
is there's no feeling in the world

00:27:18.970 --> 00:27:21.660
like finishing a draft or
finishing the whole book

00:27:21.660 --> 00:27:23.300
and feeling great about it.

00:27:23.300 --> 00:27:25.450
It's the best feeling.

00:27:25.450 --> 00:27:26.750
Yes.

00:27:26.750 --> 00:27:31.390
&gt;&gt; Hi, what is some advice you
have for young writers or writers

00:27:31.390 --> 00:27:33.300
that want to continue
writing in the future?

00:27:33.300 --> 00:27:34.600
&gt;&gt; Thank you.

00:27:34.600 --> 00:27:36.710 position:56%
My advice would be, read everything.

00:27:36.710 --> 00:27:39.970
For people, for everybody, I
would say read what you love,

00:27:39.970 --> 00:27:42.460
for writers, I say read everything.

00:27:42.460 --> 00:27:44.820
You need to know, not just the
kind of books that you write

00:27:44.820 --> 00:27:46.770
but everything that's out there.

00:27:46.770 --> 00:27:48.890
Write for fun, just write for fun,

00:27:48.890 --> 00:27:50.620
don't worry about publishing
right now,

00:27:50.620 --> 00:27:52.560
don't worry about all
that side of it.

00:27:52.560 --> 00:27:56.890
Enjoy the writing time, just
like it takes years for athletes

00:27:56.890 --> 00:27:59.490
to become professional,
or a musician,

00:27:59.490 --> 00:28:02.620
it's the same as developing
writing skills.

00:28:02.620 --> 00:28:04.820
So just enjoy it.

00:28:04.820 --> 00:28:06.130
Yeah, right here.

