00:28:37.420 --> 00:28:39.610
&gt;&gt; How did you get the idea
for Rapunzel's Revenge?

00:28:39.610 --> 00:28:41.930
&gt;&gt; Rapunzel's Revenge
came, my husband,

00:28:41.930 --> 00:28:45.740
I think this is actually our
last question, I'm so sorry,

00:28:45.740 --> 00:28:48.690
but if you find me right
afterwards, I would be happy

00:28:48.690 --> 00:28:50.300
to answer your question
and then I'm going

00:28:50.300 --> 00:28:52.840
to be signing from
3 to 4 down there.

00:28:52.840 --> 00:28:55.790
But so, Rapunzel's Revenge was a
graphic novel like a comic book

00:28:55.790 --> 00:28:57.920
that my husband and I wrote.

00:28:57.920 --> 00:29:01.300
He was a lifelong comics reader
and I didn't, was not interested

00:29:01.300 --> 00:29:03.610
in comics until I married him.

00:29:03.610 --> 00:29:07.260
And we thought, how could
bring our two loves together,

00:29:07.260 --> 00:29:08.660
my first love is fairy tales,

00:29:08.660 --> 00:29:10.250
and his first love
was super hero comics.

00:29:10.250 --> 00:29:13.140
So we were like what fairy
tale character could we turn

00:29:13.140 --> 00:29:15.130
into a comic book super hero?

00:29:15.130 --> 00:29:19.310
And we decided, Rapunzel,
because she's got that long hair.

00:29:19.310 --> 00:29:22.230
And she, when she's locked up in
her tower, she starts to practice

00:29:22.230 --> 00:29:25.140
with those braids ad use
them as whip and lasso.

00:29:25.140 --> 00:29:27.430
And so we set it in the
Old West and she escapes

00:29:27.430 --> 00:29:28.790
from the tower and becomes a hero.

00:29:28.790 --> 00:29:30.900
So that's how we came
up with that idea.

